Version Beta.3 0.7.0
=====
Major Release Updates.
BREAKING CHANGE: please update your conf file <slacker new-config>
Update: new syntax in repos file: mirror/<subpath>
Add: slacker history
slacker history --help
Show a chronological log of package changes — installed, upgraded and removed, and when — newest first. Derived from the pkgtools admin directories, so it also reflects changes made outside slacker

Usage: slacker history [OPTIONS] [NAME]

Arguments:
  [NAME]  Limit to a single package name

Options:
      --config-dir <CONFIG_DIR>  Directory holding the plain-text config files [default: /etc/slacker]
      --last <LAST>              Show only the most recent N events
      --since <SINCE>            Show only events on or after this date (YYYY-MM-DD)
  -y, --yes                      Assume "yes" to confirmation prompts
      --dry-run                  Show what would happen without changing the system
      --installed                Show only packages currently installed (with their install date)
      --no-deps                  Do not read .dep files / pull in dependencies for this run
      --removed                  Show only packages that left the system (removed or upgraded away)
      --upgraded                 Show only upgrade / reinstall events
  -h, --help                     Print help
---

Version Beta.2 0.6.0
=====
Add: protection mechanism from "rogue" or tampered repositories will be put into auto-quarantine:
slacker {trust-repo,distrust-repo,vet-repo}
Add: slacker status
Add: slacker list-repos + installed counts per repo
Add: slacker add-repo
Add: slacker del-repo
Add: slacker add-tag
Add: slacker del-tag
Add: option immutable a repo
Fix: bug with staled changelogs on 3rd repos
Fix: bug in install-new
Fix: bug with testing,extras,patches,pasture url`s
NEW: slacker clean-system will remove all packages that not exist in slackware PACKAGES.TXT
(excluded blacklisted packages, @repo packages and _tags in /etc/slacker.conf) This way will also be removed
packages that distro official remove.
NOTE: packages from testing extras must be mentioned in blacklist.
